<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1887,2030]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,152,294]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="19" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1965,1991]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
As currently defined this species is confined to 
<collectingRegion box="[913,1001,1965,1991]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Hawaii</collectingRegion>
. Other Pacific records are of a new species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webb &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2009" box="[257,341,2004,2029]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="knighti">
<emphasis box="[257,341,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">knighti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) described below (see Appendix 5). It differs from 
<emphasis box="[974,1067,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">knightii</emphasis>
by the apical extension of the aedeagus being broader in lateral view (compare 
<figureCitation box="[746,956,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–39" captionStartId="55.[151,275,1727,1751]" captionTargetBox="[170,1369,193,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-65@55.[151,1436,133,1808]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 38–39. Maiestas species. 38, M. hospes (Kirkaldy), o–q: aedeagus, lateral, dorsal and ventral view respectively (lectotype, except a, k, m, n, W.J. Knight originals). 39, M. knighti sp. nov., o: aedeagus, lateral view (o: Australia; remainder (except a, n, W.J. Knight originals), holotype New Zealand)." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 38k and 39k</figureCitation>
) and more laterally compressed basally (compare 
<figureCitation box="[271,497,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–39" captionStartId="55.[151,275,1727,1751]" captionTargetBox="[170,1369,193,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-65@55.[151,1436,133,1808]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 38–39. Maiestas species. 38, M. hospes (Kirkaldy), o–q: aedeagus, lateral, dorsal and ventral view respectively (lectotype, except a, k, m, n, W.J. Knight originals). 39, M. knighti sp. nov., o: aedeagus, lateral view (o: Australia; remainder (except a, n, W.J. Knight originals), holotype New Zealand)." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Figs 
<quantity box="[330,383,190,216]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="m" value="38.0">38m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[442,497,190,216]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="m" value="39.0">39m</quantity>
</figureCitation>
) and the style apical process being more robust (compare 
<figureCitation box="[1194,1397,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 38–39" captionStartId="55.[151,275,1727,1751]" captionTargetBox="[170,1369,193,1686]" captionTargetId="figure-65@55.[151,1436,133,1808]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURES 38–39. Maiestas species. 38, M. hospes (Kirkaldy), o–q: aedeagus, lateral, dorsal and ventral view respectively (lectotype, except a, k, m, n, W.J. Knight originals). 39, M. knighti sp. nov., o: aedeagus, lateral view (o: Australia; remainder (except a, n, W.J. Knight originals), holotype New Zealand)." pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Figs 38f and 39f</figureCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Knight" authorityYear="1976" box="[305,440,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="samuelsoni">
<emphasis box="[305,440,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">samuelsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) only in its broader subgenital plate. We have examined the 
<typeStatus box="[1325,1436,229,255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">lectotype</typeStatus>
male, (designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fletcher, M. J. &amp; Condello, A. A." box="[401,761,268,294]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="35 - 59" refId="ref15547" refString="Fletcher, M. J. &amp; Condello, A. A. (1993). Lectotype designations and new synonymies for G. W. Kirkaldy's Australian Deltocephalinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) held in the B. P. Bishop Museum, Honolulu. General and Applied Entomology, 25, 35 - 59." type="journal article" year="1993">Fletcher &amp; Condello, 1993: 43</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<typeStatus box="[826,984,268,294]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">paralectotype</typeStatus>
male, 
<collectingRegion box="[1063,1148,268,294]" country="United States of America" name="Hawaii" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Hawaii</collectingRegion>
(BPBM), of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirkaldy. Subsequent" authorityYear="1904" box="[1303,1383,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Deltocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hospes">
<emphasis box="[1303,1383,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">hospes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
